Given n of 1 or more, return the factorial of n, which is n * (n-1) * (n-2) ... 1. Compute the result recursively (without loops).


factorial(1) → 1
factorial(2) → 2
factorial(3) → 6

My solution
public int factorial(int n) {
  int result = 0;
  if(n==1){
    result = 1;
  }
  result = n;
  while (n!=1){
    result = result*(n-1);
    n--;
  }
  return result;
}

Solution from Internet

public int factorial(int n) {

  if (n == 0) return 1;

  return n * factorial(n-1);

}
